                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <input asp-for="visualization_probe3z" class="form-control" />
                        <span asp-validation-for="visualization_probe3z" class="text-danger" />
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
 
        <!-- Cutting planes -->
        <br /><br /><br />
        <h5><strong>Cutting planes</strong></h5>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-3">
                <br />
                All geometrical properties have standardized measure by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_System_of_Units">SI Units</a>. Coordinates are in meters!
                <br /><br />
                First choose the number of cutting planes and then set up the coordinates.
                <br />
                In total there are two spatial points that have to be set up. Each plane requires a point and a normal to be fully defined.
                <br />
                Point in space defines location of plane whereas normal defines it's orientation.
                <br /><br />
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label asp-for="visualization_numCuts" class="col-md-6 control-label" style="text-align:right;"></label>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <input asp-for="visualization_numCuts" class="form-control" id="numCuts" />
